Saudi Arabia’s National Water Signs $375 Million Supply Deal

-- B y   S a r a h   A b d u l l a h
-- 
2011-12-07T14:33:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-07/saudi-arabia-s-national-water-signs-375-million-supply-deal.html
National Water Co.,  Saudi Arabia ’s
state-owned utility, signed a 30-year agreement worth $375
million with Huta Group.  The deal is to supply treated wastewater to Huta Hegerfeld,
a unit of the engineering company, National Water’s Chief
Executive Officer Loay Musallam said today at a signing ceremony
today in  Jeddah , Saudi Arabia. The water is for use at the Jabar
Omar residential and commercial center in Mecca, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
